column23:
You are invited to participate in this survey whose main purpose is to take an instructional look at question and structures of a survey itself. This survey is part of research designed by students and faculty at the University of Massachusetts Amherst. Your participation in this study is completely voluntary and you can withdraw at any time. The survey should take about 8 - 11 minutes to complete.


The information you will share with us if you participate in this study will be kept completely confidential to the full extent of the law.

column186: They both work full-time, 40 hours per week and their contributions to household income are almost identical. They share equal responsibility for childcare and split household tasks (e.g. laundry, dishwashing, meal-prep, cleaning…) 50/50.
column192: In “Review on Community Food Security and Edible Insects Resources: Biodiversity and Policy Implications for Safeguarding Human Consumption” Monica Ayieko (2013) states “Climate change is affecting agriculture and food production in a complex way. It has impact on human health, livestock, livelihood assets, food production and distribution channels that ensures that the food is placed on consumers’ table [sic] on time. Because it affects consumer purchasing power and market flow, it changes consumers’ food consumption pattern. Many family members are experimenting with new foods and many other consumers are willing to consume new food items not familiar to them. The climate change also influences food safety and quality that go with it all (Schmidhuber and Tubiello, 2007)."

Because it affects consumer purchasing power and market flow, it changes consumers’ food consumption pattern. Many family members are experimenting with new foods and many other consumers are willing to consume new food items not familiar to them. The climate change also influences food safety and quality that go with it all (Schmidhuber and Tubiello, 2007)."
